==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interject
<hw>In`ter*ject"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Interjected</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Interjecting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>interjectus</ets>,
p. p. of <ets>interjicere</ets> to interject; <ets>inter</ets> between +
<ets>jac⟦ecr⟧re</ets> to throw. See <er>Jet</er> a shooting
forth.]</ety> <def>To throw in between; to insert; to interpose.</def>
<rj><au>Sir H. Wotton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interject</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Interject
<hw>In`ter*ject"</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To throw one's self between
or among; to come between; to interpose.</def> <rj><au>Sir G.
Buck.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interjection</ent>⟦br⟧
